            "27 April 2002",
            "Swedish-born wide player with plenty of talent and unpredictability.\n" + "\n" + "The youngster has pace to burn and is capable of creating havoc down the flanks. He made his Under-18s Premier League North debut as a schoolboy, coming on as a substitute in the final match of the division at Liverpool.\n" + "\n" + "He made his mark during the 2018/19 term as a first-year scholar, scoring four times in 22 appearances for Neil Ryan's side, including a Goal-of-the Month contender against Newcastle United in March, following a mazy dribble.\n" + "\n" + "The following season, he was voted the Jimmy Murphy Young Player of the Year and was close to scoring an incredible goal during the narrow FA Youth Cup semi-final defeat to Chelsea at St George's Park.\n" + "\n" + "A first glimpse of senior action arrived in the club's only pre-season friendly, at Aston Villa, when he came on as a second-half substitute and he became a key attacking weapon for Neil Wood's Under-23s, upsetting defenders with his pace and directness. An excellent display against Salford City in the Papa John's Trophy also showed he could compete with older, more experienced markers.\n" + "\n" + "On 16 March 2021, he signed a new long-term contract with the club and, after being drafted into the Europa League squad, he made a Premier League debut against Leicester City on 11 May, starting the game at Old Trafford. It came shortly after another impressive outing at Premier League 2 level, when he scored twice in a 6-2 thumping of Derby County at Loughborough University.\n" + "\n" + "The 2021/22 season saw Elanga breakthrough into the first team and become a regular. Despite not featuring until December, the Swedish winger ended the campaign with 27 senior appearances in all competitions.\n" + "\n" + "Elanga scored three goals in all competitions for the Reds in 2021/22, including his first-ever Champions League goal – a brilliant equaliser in the last 16 against Atletico Madrid at the Wanda Metropolitano.\n" + "\n" + "The winger's scintillating club form also earned him a first call-up to the Sweden squad in March 2022, and he followed this up with his first international goal against Norway on 5 June.",
